## Step 1 — Load context

You are working inside a repository.

Load and follow these files as permanent context:

- .claude/context/role.md
- .claude/context/rules.md
- .claude/context/conventions.md

Confirm when loaded.

## Step 2 — Pipeline overview

Each task moves through a fixed pipeline. Every stage produces an artifact file in:

.claude/specs/tasks/{TASK_ID}/

| Stage             | Input                                                 | Workflow                       | Output                    | Skill        |
| ----------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------ | ------------------------- | ------------ |
| 1. Spec           | 00-raw-task.md + ui/ screenshots                      | task-to-spec.md                | 02-spec.md                | /spec        |
| 2. Spec review    | 00-raw-task.md + 02-spec.md                           | review-spec.md                 | 03-spec-review.md         | /review-spec |
| 3. Plan           | 02-spec.md + 03-spec-review.md                        | spec-to-implementation-plan.md | 04-implementation-plan.md | /plan or /plan-fullstack |
| 4. Implementation | 04-implementation-plan.md                             | — (write code)                 | source files              | —            |
| 5. Code review    | source files + 02-spec.md + 04-implementation-plan.md | code-review.md                 | 05-code-review.md         | /code-review |
| 6. Done           | source files + all spec docs                          | implementation-done.md         | 06-implementation-done.md | /done        |

## Step 3 — Run pipeline

### Option A: Use skills (recommended)

```
/spec {TASK_ID}
/review-spec {TASK_ID}
/plan {TASK_ID}              ← frontend-only or simple single-concern task
/plan-fullstack {TASK_ID}    ← fullstack task (backend + frontend, parallel agents)
... implement code ...
/code-review {TASK_ID}
/done {TASK_ID}
```

### When to use /plan vs /plan-fullstack

| Use `/plan` when... | Use `/plan-fullstack` when... |
|---------------------|-------------------------------|
| Task touches only the frontend (UI, components, pages) | Task requires both backend and frontend changes |
| Task touches only the backend (DB migration, edge function) | New feature needs a DB schema + API endpoint + UI |
| Simple single-concern change (styling, copy, a single hook) | Task involves a new API contract between layers |
| You want a fast, single-agent plan | Spec describes data flow from DB → API → UI |
| | You want integration gaps caught before implementation |

### Option B: Manual workflow invocation

```
claude run .claude/workflows/task-to-spec.md --var TASK_ID={TASK_ID}
claude run .claude/workflows/review-spec.md --var TASK_ID={TASK_ID}
claude run .claude/workflows/spec-to-implementation-plan.md --var TASK_ID={TASK_ID}
claude run .claude/workflows/code-review.md --var TASK_ID={TASK_ID}
claude run .claude/workflows/implementation-done.md --var TASK_ID={TASK_ID}
```

---

## Gate rules

- Stage 3 (Plan) cannot proceed if Stage 2 result is FAIL.
- Stage 5 (Code review) cannot proceed without Stage 3 artifact.
- Stage 6 (Done) cannot proceed without Stages 3 and 5 artifacts.
